title.narrative: OUTPUT 5.4 CHILD PROTECTION SERVICES

description.narrative: Output 4 (Child protection services): Child protection services at national and subnational levels have improved capacities to provide accessible prevention and response social welfare, justice and civil registration services that meet minimum standards., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys are progressively empowered and protected from violence, exploitation, neglect and harmful practices by functioning, quality child protection systems and positive social norms at national and subnational level including in humanitarian settings.

title.narrative: Output 4 (Child protection services): Child protection services at national and subnational levels have improved capacities toprovide accessible prevention and response social welfare, justice and civil registration services that meet minimum standards.

description.narrative: UNICEF supported key ministries to strengthen the provision of protection services for vulnerable and at-risk children by developing service standards, building capacities of key stakeholders at the national and subnational levels and introducing accountability platforms. During the first year of the Country Programme, UNICEF also strengthened the linkages between protection services for children and women while enhancing accessibility at community levels by establishing comprehensive protection services and improving referral pathways.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
